1 determine whether the order complies with subsection (2) of this section.
2 If the Governor determines that any order does not comply with subsection
3 (2) of this section, then the Governor shall take any action necessary to
4 immediately return such members of the Nebraska National Guard to
5 Nebraska.
6 (4) The Governor shall submit a report to the Government, Military
7 and Veterans Affairs Committee of the Legislature that summarizes the
8 Governor's review of the federal orders and any action that the Governor
9 took in response to that review, within thirty days after the review is
10 completed.
11 (5) For the purposes of this section, active combat means:
12 (a) Participation in an armed conflict;
13 (b) Performance of a hazardous service relating to an armed conflict
14 in a foreign state; or
15 (c) Performance of a duty through an instrumentality of war.
16 Sec. 2. Original section 55-118, Reissue Revised Statutes of
17 Nebraska, is repealed.
